git rm --cached .env
git rm --cached .webui_secret_key
git rm -r --cached data models logs run env1
git commit -m "Remove private runtime files"
git push
Then regenerate any exposed secrets.

.gitignore does not secure the app itself
It is important to understand:

.gitignore protects the GitHub repository.

It does not replace:

Strong permissions
Secret key generation
Local-only binding to 127.0.0.1
Authentication
Your check-security.sh
Safe systemd configuration
Your installer already handles those runtime protections.

.gitignore is mainly for preventing accidental leaks on GitHub.

